HOW TO USE THE DOCTORS/CONSULTATION PANEL

1. To access the Doctor’s panel click on Doctor tile on the Dashboard

2. When a patient is queued in Consultation room, the patient record will be available in

doctor’s mini queue list

3. Select the patient by clicking on his name once, the patients demographics will be

displayed in patient’s details section. You can also call a patient by right clicking and

select call Patient.

4. Selected patient is highlighted in blue. Clerk the patient on provided fields.

5. After filling each field ensure you press the blue plus button to save

6. Once you are done recording required details, click on Actions button. Click on Queue

Patient then queue patient to next room.

7. Under actions list you can perform various actions such as;

 Refer a patient

![](data:image/png;base64,)

 Clerk in patients vitals

 Add Physical Examinations

 Make a lab request

 Make a radiology request

 Make a theatre request

 Make an appointment

 Assess and plan for the patient

 Make a prescription

 Queue the patient

 Bill a Patient

 Pick a patient in admission

 View the visit summary

 View a lab report

 View theatre report

 View examination report

 View all visit report

HOW TO MAKE A PRESCRIPTION

1. To make a prescription, select prescription from Actions, the window below will appear

i. Select prescription type i.e. Drug, Non-Stock or Procedure

ii. Select the storage location if you wish to prescribe a drug from a different storage

location

iii. Select the item you want to prescribe

iv. Select the scheme you want to bill the prescription against

v. Enter quantity per time

vi. Select the dosage unit

vii. Enter the frequency per day

viii. Enter the duration i.e. number of days

ix. Select the period i.e. days or weeks

x. The system will automatically calculate the total number of drugs

xi. As you make the prescription the system automatically indicates the dosage

instructions

xii. Enter the transcription

xiii. Enter the prescription(special Instructions)

xiv. Click on Add button to save the prescription

xv. Click on view Report to view the prescription report

After saving the prescription you can queue the patient to the Cash office so that the patient

can pay or invoiced for the drugs

HOW TO CLERK PATIENT VITALS

1\. To Clerk in patient’s vitals, select Vitals from Actions list

2\. The window below will appear

![](data:image/png;base64,)

3\. Select a general Examination, add a Remark/Result against the examination then click on Add(+)

4\. Select a procedure and click on Add(+)

5\. Fill the body system and add a remark, tick the checkbox if anomalous and click on Add(+)

6\. Add nursing notes and save.

7\. Close the window and go to the next required action.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

HOW TO MAKE A LAB REQUEST FOR A PATIENT

1. On Doctor’s panel, click Actions button. This provides a list of options.

2. Click on Lab Request

3. Select patient scheme and the required test and click on Add (+) button

4. Add all required tests. Then queue the patient to the next point depending on your

workflow.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

HOW TO MAKE APPOINTMENTS FOR A PATIENT

1. In the doctors panel select the name of the patient you want to schedule for an

appointment

2. Click on Actions button and select Appointment from the list.

3. The window below will come into view

![](data:image/png;base64,)

4. Fill in the name of doctor making the appointment, email address of the patient,

Appointment date and time, purpose of the appointment

5. After filling these fields then click on Schedule Appointment button.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

HOW TO QUEUE A PATIENT

1. To queue a patient to the next room

2. Click on Queue Patient under Actions

3. The window below will appear

![](data:image/png;base64,)

4\. Select the room you want to queue the patient e.g. Cash office

5\. Check Is Emergency if it’s an emergency case (the patients name will appear in red color)

6\. Add a note that you would like to appear on patients’ queue

7\. Click on Queue Patient

![](data:image/png;base64,)

HOW TO REFER A PATIENT

1. Select Actions and click on Refer Patient, the window below will appear

2. Fill in the required fields and click on save. You can view and print the referral Report by

selecting the saved referral at the bottom and click on View Referral Report at the top

of referral panel
